  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Published by Leuven University Press in 2023, \"Tot de bodem\" has yet to make a significant mark in terms of citations and community discourse. Its current metrics indicate a developing academic presence, with initial interest noted in commercial platforms like Amazon and Goodreads.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">\"Tot de bodem,\" released by Leuven University Press in 2023, represents an emerging scholarly work that is beginning to carve out its space within the academic landscape. While the book currently shows no recorded citations, the presence of commercial linkages through platforms such as Amazon and Goodreads suggests that it may attract interest from readers beyond academia, potentially enhancing its visibility over time.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">At this early stage, the lack of community engagement on platforms known for high-fidelity social discourse, including Wikipedia, Reddit, and Bluesky, indicates a need for greater outreach and promotion within both academic and public spheres. This absence further emphasizes the work's nascent stage of impact within the community and its potential for future discussions.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The metrics compiled so far are valuable in understanding the initial reception of \"Tot de bodem.\" The inferred roles evidence a strong commercial appeal; with a strength rating of 0.9 in commercial linkage, this suggests a promising path towards greater scholarly uptake as the book gains more visibility. The strength rating of 0.45 for scholarly uptake indicates early signals that could evolve into meaningful academic dialogue.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">As the narrative surrounding \"Tot de bodem\" continues to develop, future metrics will be necessary to gauge substantial academic engagement and community response. Monitoring platform activities and citation trends will be crucial in assessing the long-term impact of this publication in its respective field and beyond.</p>",
